        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 11:29AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1128 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Monroeton, or near Reidsville, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Eden...
Reidsville...
Wentworth...
Yanceyville...
Bethel...
and Stoneville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
